# Aider ignore - tuned for large Rust monorepos and LLM token efficiency
# =====================================================================
# Guidelines:
# - Keep global build, editor and noise files ignored.
# - Layer masking blocks are provided below. Uncomment a block to IGNORE
#   that entire architectural layer from Aider's repo-map generation.
# - Uncommenting reduces map size / token usage; keep inner layers visible
#   (kernel, domain) by default for accurate reasoning unless you need to
#   further reduce tokens.

# ------------------------
# Global noise / build
# ------------------------
target/
.git/
.idea/
.vscode/
Cargo.lock
*.rs.bk
*.tmp
*.log

# ------------------------
# Layer masking blocks
# ------------------------
# Each block targets the crate-name prefixes used in this workspace.
# To reduce tokens, uncomment the entire block for the layer(s) you do not
# need Aider to map right now. Leave commented to include them.

# KERNEL (lowest-level primitives) — recommended: keep visible
# To IGNORE kernel crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-kernel-*/

# DOMAIN (business logic) — recommended: keep visible
# To IGNORE domain crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-domain-*/

# CORE (engines, orchestrators)
# To IGNORE core crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-core-*/

# APPLICATION (use-cases, services)
# To IGNORE application crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-application-*/

# INTELLIGENCE (AI orchestration, often large/noisy)
# To IGNORE intelligence crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-intelligence-*/

# INTERFACE (CLI/UI surface, frequently changing)
# To IGNORE interface crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-interface-*/

# INFRASTRUCTURE (IO, external integrations)
# To IGNORE infrastructure crates, uncomment the next line:
# zaroxi-infrastructure-*/

# ------------------------
# Fine-grained examples
# ------------------------
# Uncomment single crate folders to ignore them specifically (examples):
# zaroxi-interface-desktop/
# zaroxi-infrastructure-memory/
# zaroxi-core-platform-syntax/

# ------------------------
# Whitelisting / overrides
# ------------------------
# If Aider supports gitignore-style negation you can add explicit keep rules:
# Example (uncomment if supported by your Aider version):
# !zaroxi-kernel-*/src/lib.rs

# ------------------------
# Notes for maintainers
# ------------------------
# - Prefer toggling whole-layer blocks over per-crate toggles when iterating.
# - Keep this file minimal and explicit: large, generic globs cause accidental
#   omission of critical crates.
# - This file scales to 140+ crates because masks are prefix-based and layer-oriented.
